HEADWORD: coolheaded
<hw>cool"head*ed</hw></mhw> <pr>(?)</pr>,
<pos>a.</pos> <def>Having a temper not easily excited; free from
passion; unshakably calm and collected.</def> --
<wordforms><wf>Cool"-head`ed*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> cool, imperturbable, unflappable.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> + <source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Coolie</ent>⟦br⟧
